==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hostile takeover
<hw>hostile takeover</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Finance)</fld> <def>the
purchase of a controlling interest in a publicly-traded company against
the wishes of the current management.</def> <note>A person who is the
main principal in performing such a buyout is called a <er>corporate
raider</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hostile buyout.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hostilities</ent>⟦br⟧
